{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"440d0b78-4522-4f7f-9386-d3b8abfc6f46","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n1. **Update NUnit3TestAdapter** to **4.6.0+** (you're already there ✅).\n\n2. **Add the platform package**:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable the new platform** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Add a `Program.cs` entry point** (or use the auto-generated one by setting `<GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>`, which is the default).\n\n5. **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's replaced by the new platform packages.\n\n6. Run tests with `dotnet test` as before — the new platform is used under the hood.\n\n**Optional but recommended**: add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` or `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` if you need TRX output or coverage, since those are no longer bundled via the old SDK package.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1138478e-18e5-40b0-bcea-1108f914022d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":378,"requestId":"4811:301230:30816BA:3510F65:69FBE1CD"},"id":"11e07eae-1aba-417d-979f-3fa7ddb325dd","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:50:30.717Z","parentId":"bdeff244-86d5-4068-8f80-7db19a0e7ae3"}
